$ Shell command: iconv
@ iconv

`iconv` convertes text from one → development/Unicode/character-encoding to another.

{ Example


code { 
$ iconv -f UTF8 -t LATIN1 foo.txt > foo.latin1.txt
code }
This converts a UTF 8 encoded file `foo.txt` into a latin 1 encoded file named `foo.latin1.txt`.

}



sa:

  → Linux/shell/commands/file#file-determine-character-encoding[`file`] can be used to determine the encoding of files.

  → Linux/shell/commands/recode

  → development/Unicode/character-encoding-known

  → Linux/shell/commands/index[Shell commands]
